'''Omar Abdillahi Charmarke''' (born 1954) is a [[Djibouti]]an long-distance runner who specialized in the marathon.

Charmarke was a member of the first ever [[Djibouti]] Olympic team, when he and two others entered the [[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics – Men's marathon|marathon]] at the [[1984 Summer Olympics]] held in [[Los Angeles]], he finished 32nd in the race.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ch/omar-abdillahi-charmarke-1.html Sports Reference Profile]</ref>

