{{Infobox venue | name = Stade Marcel-Deflandre | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = [[File:Stade rochelais tribune.jpg|260px]] | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[La Rochelle]], [[France]] | coordinates = {{coord|46|09|29|N|1|10|41|W|source:kolossus-frwiki|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{Start date|1926|09|26}} | renovated = 2010 | expanded = {{Start date|1995|05|02}} | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 16,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[Stade Rochelais]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Stade Marcel-Deflandre''' is a [[sports stadium]] in [[La Rochelle]], [[France]]. It was built by Emile Sourcile. It is the home ground of [[rugby union]] team [[Stade Rochelais]] of the [[Top 14]] who have played there since it was opened in 1926. It has undergone significant redevelopment since 1995 and the present capacity is 16,000 (2,500 added during summer 2014). The stadium is named after [[Marcel Deflandre]], a president of the club who was executed in 1944 during the [[Second World War]].
