The '''Taroko Gorge Marathon''' ([https://www.taroko-marathon.com.tw/ official website]) is an annual [[marathon]] running race held in [[Taroko National Park]] in [[Taiwan]]. It is organised by the [[Chinese Taipei Road Running Association]].
The race is held in November each year and the marathon and half-marathon had a combined 10,500 runners in 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=Taroko Gorge Marathon to add 500 runners this Nov|url=http://www.chinapost.com.tw/taiwan/local/hualien/2011/07/11/309400/Taroko-Gorge.htm|accessdate=22 July 2012|newspaper=The China Post}}</ref> It usually sells out within a week or two.
